 Here's a summary of what was built:

  Customer 360 v1 — Implementation Summary

  What was implemented

  Full projection-backed customer workspace at /customers/[id]/360 — the first product page built on the new Omni architecture.

  Customer Identity Bar (sticky, z-10)
  - Account name + live subscription status pill + delinquency flag
  - ARR headline, domain, owner/CSM, account type
  - "New Quote" and contextual "Renewal" action buttons (shown only when urgency is not on_track)

  Stat Strip — Bloomberg-density horizontal bar: MRR, ARR, balance, contract end, subscription count — all from real projection data

  Signal Strip — derived dynamically from projection data: delinquency, past-due subscription, cancelAtPeriodEnd, renewal urgency (overdue/critical/due_soon),
  DNR flag, healthy indicator. No hardcoded signals.

  3-column layout: tabbed main area + sticky right action rail
  - Overview tab: account details + active contract fields (2-col grid) + inline Renewal panel with urgency/ARR/DNR/workflow status
  - Subscriptions tab: per-subscription panels with items, MRR, period, linked contract
  - Invoices tab: invoice list with status, amounts, hosted URL links

  Action Rail (right, sticky): Quick Actions (Create Quote, Prepare Renewal), Ownership (AE/CSM), External Links (SF/Stripe), System IDs with copy buttons, Sync
   Status

  Files changed

  - app/(app)/customers/[id]/360/page.tsx — rewritten: Server Component loader using projections; resolves SF Account ID → CustomerIndex.id; parallel-fetches
  subscriptions + invoices + renewal
  - app/(app)/customers/[id]/360/customer-360.tsx — rewritten: no mock data, all real projection types; full page composition
  - app/(app)/customers/[id]/page.tsx — added "360 View" button to navigate to the new workspace
  - app/(app)/contracts/[id]/page.tsx — removed pre-existing unused Link import (cleanup)

  No forbidden paths introduced

  - Zero lib/queries/* imports in the new 360 page
  - Zero components/workspace/* imports
  - mock-data.ts is untouched (already has DELETE BEFORE WIRING header) — the page no longer imports from it

